        \begin {tikzcd}
            Q \\
            \\
            {\prod _{i\in  I} X_i} && {X_i}
            \arrow ["{p_i}", from=3-1, to=3-3]
            \arrow ["{f_i}", from=1-1, to=3-3]
            \arrow ["{(f_i)_{i\in  I}}"', from=1-1, to=3-1]
        \end {tikzcd}

A terminal object in a category \mathcal {C} is an object \top  of \mathcal {C} 
    satisfying the following universal property: for any object X in \mathcal {C},
    there exists a unique morphism !:X\to  \top .

For \mathcal {C} a category and X, Y \in \text {Ob}{\mathcal {C}},
    the coproduct is an object X\sqcup   Y equipped with 
    two morphisms i_X:X\to  X\sqcup   Y and i_Y:Y\to  X\sqcup   Y such that
    it is universal with this property. That is, for any object Z and morphisms
    f:X\to  Z and g:Y\to  Z, there exists a unique morphism \langle  f, g\rangle :X\sqcup   Y\to  Z
    such that the following diagram commutes:





